<html xmlns:MadCap="http://www.madcapsoftware.com/Schemas/MadCap.xsd" MadCap:conditions="Products.Analyzer,Products.Contributor,Products.Flare" MadCap:lastBlockDepth="2" MadCap:lastHeight="150" MadCap:lastWidth="832">
    <body>
        <p>Opens the Update Cross-References dialog, which lets you update the cross-references that you have added to topics<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Contributor"> or documents</MadCap:conditionalText>. By updating the cross-references, you can ensure that they reflect any changes <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Flare,Products.Analyzer">in your project </MadCap:conditionalText>that might affect them. </p>
        <p>Updating cross-references is not a mandatory step. When you generate output<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Flare,Products.Analyzer"> for a target</MadCap:conditionalText>, all of your cross-references will be updated automatically. <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Flare,Products.Analyzer">However, you can use this feature to manually update cross-references in a single topic. This is a way of performing a "spot check" ahead of time, verifying that cross-references will be updated accurately before you generate the entire target.</MadCap:conditionalText></p>
    </body>
</html>